Environmental Programs

The environmental management system at Cloud Peak Energy incorporates elements that continue to be certified under ISO-14001 standards since 2005. The program consists of an internationally recognized management system of policies, objectives and targets:

Accounting for legal requirements, voluntary commitments beyond legal environmental compliance, and significant environmental aspects
Facilitating environmental protection and prevention of pollution in balance with socio-economic needs
Incorporating environmental considerations into Cloud Peak Energy business planning and decisions
Followed by all persons working for or on behalf of Cloud Peak Energy
The system incorporates:

Commitment from all levels and functions of the organization, including top management, for establishment and continual improvement of a system that controls and minimizes potential environmental impacts of the operation
Identification of the environmental aspects of operational activities, products and services that can be controlled and/or influenced, and developed management and control strategies for those determined to have potential significance
Availability of resources essential to establish, implement, maintain and improve the environmental management system
Defined, documented and communicated roles, responsibilities and authorities in order to facilitate effective environmental management
Established, implemented and maintained procedures to identify and address potential emergency or incident situations that can have environmental impacts
Internal monitoring procedures to measure performance and key characteristics of the operation that can have a significant environmental impact
Internal auditing procedures to evaluate the performance of the environmental management system and compliance with legal and other requirements
Specific procedures to address actual and potential nonconformance with legal and other requirements
Procedures for top management review of the suitability, adequacy and effectiveness of the environmental management system



