afe Sam Award) for no lost time accidents – Antelope Mine  1999 Sentinels of Safety Award, Large Surface Coal Mine, by the U.S. Department of Labor – Cordero Rojo Mine  1999 Safest Surface Coal Mine from the Office of the State Mine Inspector – Cordero Rojo Mine  1998 Sentinels of Safety Award, Large Surface Coal Mine, by the U.S. Department of Labor – Cordero Rojo Mine  1997 Wyoming/Montana Safety Council Award – Spring Creek Mine  1996 Wyoming Governor's Safety Award – Antelope Mine  1996 Wyoming/Montana Safety Council Award – Spring Creek Mine  1994 Wyoming Governor's Safety Award – Antelope Mine   Cloud Peak Energy Environmental Awards 2010 National Excellence in Surface Mining and Reclamation from the Office of Surface Mining and National Mining Association for shrub development on reclaimed lands establishing wildlife habitat – Antelope Mine  2010 Wyoming Excellence in Surface Mining and Reclamation Award from the Wyoming Department of Environmental Quality for shrub development on reclaimed lands establishing wildlife habitat – Antelope Mine   2009 Wildlife Habitat Reclamation and Stewardship Award from the Wyoming Game and Fish Department for accomplishments in Mountain Plover habitat – Antelope Mine   2009 National Excellence in Surface Mining and Reclamation from the Office of Surface Mining for achievements in establishing and maintaining a rare plant species, the woolly twinpod – Spring Creek Mine  2006 Excellence in Surface Coal Mining and Reclamation Award, from the Wyoming Department of Environmental Quality for designed riverbed reconstruction – Cordero Rojo Mine  2005 National Excellence in Surface Mining and Reclamation from the Office of Surface Mining for achievements in establishing excellent topographic and vegetative diversity of the South Fork reclamation – Spring Creek Mine   2003 National Excellence in Surface Coal Mining and Reclamation Award from the Office of Surface Mining for prairie dog relocation project – Antelope Mine  2003 Wyoming Excellence in Surface Mining and Reclamation Award from the Wyoming Department of Environmental Quality for prairie dog relocation project – Antelope Mine  2003 Wildlife Habitat Reclamation and Stewardship Award from the Wyoming Game & Fish Department for prairie dog relocation project – Antelope Mine  2003 Pat Baumann, Antelope Mine, was named Habitat Conservationist of the Year by the Wyoming Wildlife Federation – Antelope Mine  1999 Excellence in Surface Coal Mining and Reclamation Award from the Wyoming Department of Environmental Quality - Land Quality Division for construction of reclaimed area wetlands – Cordero Rojo Mine  1998 Wildlife Habitat Reclamation and Stewardship Award from the Wyoming Game and Fish Department for accomplishments in establishing wetlands using detention dikes and pit pumpage water – Cordero Rojo Mine  1996 Excellence in Surface Coal Mining Permitting, Honorable Mention; from the Wyoming Department of Environmental Quality - Land Quality Division permitting efforts on the Belle Fourche River diversion – Cordero Rojo Mine 展开商品Coalcategories本地服务 · 矿业公司商家故事Big Metal and the Crow Tribe signed an Exploration Agreement and an Option to Lease Agreement on January 24, 2013 during a signing ceremony in Crow Agency. These agreements were approved by the U.S. Bureau of Indian Affairs (BIA) and provide Big Metal the opportunity to explore and define up to 1.4 billion tons of in-place coal in the southwestern portion of the Reservation and to potentially exer...cise rights to lease all or portions of this coal for mining, subject to additional regulatory approvals.  If Big Metal exercises its options to lease, mining on the Reservation likely would be supported by the existing operations and rail loadout infrastructure at Cloud Peak Energy’s Spring Creek Mine, which is located in Montana just off the Reservation to the east. The high-quality, low-sulfur Crow coal could meet demand for electric generating stations in the U.S. or Asia, helping to provide a safe, reliable and affordable source of energy and significant economic opportunity for the Crow Tribe.  Comments are welcomed and encouraged on Big Metal Coal Company LLC's Facebook page. This Facebook page serves as a positive resource for information regarding the Big Metal Project. Any comments that contain profanity or are obscene or defamatory will be deleted. Please remember that your comments may remain online for a long period of time, therefore they should be carefully considered before posting. The right to remove comments is reserved for those whose posts take the conversation considerably off topic, attack other posts, contain spam or repeat commentary. Any user who repeatedly violates the terms stated here will be blocked from commenting on this page.  The opinions and or views expressed on Big Metal Coal Company LLC's Facebook page represent the thoughts of individual posters, and not those necessarily of Cloud Peak Energy or any of its respective executive team, employees, contractors or members of its respective board of directors. The opinions and views expressed on these pages do not in any way reflect the views of the site they are posted on, other sites affiliated with the site, the staff involved with maintaining the site or any members of the site.  展开地点Crow Agency, Montana工商业Big Metal Coal Company LLC简介中文(简体)English (US)日本語한국어Français (France)Bahasa IndonesiaPolskiEspañolPortuguês (Brasil)DeutschItalianoMessengerFacebook Lite用户地点游戏位置名人二手市场小组食谱彩色气球Instagram公司简介创建广告创建主页开发者招聘信息隐私权政策Cookie广告选项条款设置活动日志 Facebook © 2017




